% Phantom Codes — bibliography (BibTeX format).
%
% Single source of truth for the paper's references. Cited from
% sections/*.md via [@Key] syntax; pandoc converts to \autocite{Key};
% biblatex+biber resolve at build time using the style configured in
% paper/main.tex (default: authoryear).
%
% Convention: each entry is preceded by a "% Why we cite:" comment
% block describing the rationale. Comments are stripped from the PDF
% but preserved here as the author's reading notes.
%
% Citation key format: <LastName><Year> (e.g., Soroush2024). Multi-token
% organizational authors collapse to acronym (CMS2026, PhysioNet2025).
% Multi-author titles use first-author surname.
%
% To add a new entry: paste the @article{...} block below, prefixed by
% a % Why we cite: ... comment. Then cite from prose with [@NewKey].

